                HStack {
                    VStack(alignment: .leading, spacing: 4) {
                        Text("2026 JPY Trade")
                            .font(.title2.weight(.bold))
                        Text("JPY weakness / intervention-test thesis with tactical short-Nikkei confirmation.")
                            .font(.subheadline)
                            .foregroundStyle(.secondary)
                    }
                    Spacer()
                    Label("Monitoring Active", systemImage: "dot.radiowaves.left.and.right")
                        .font(.caption.weight(.bold))
                        .foregroundStyle(.green)
                        .padding(.horizontal, 10)
                        .padding(.vertical, 6)
                        .background(Color.green.opacity(0.12))
                        .clipShape(RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius: 8))
                }
                Text("Core thesis: Fed hawkishness plus unclear BOJ posture can keep pressure on JPY beyond 160 and possibly toward 162. The market is testing the BOJ/MOF pain threshold, and JGBs are now the primary confirmation gauge. The yen-strengthening trade only improves if Japan shifts from unclear verbal posture to credible intervention, JGB/rate pressure, or May 22 CPI confirmation. Short Nikkei remains tactical, only after May 8 / May 13 blue-chip fatigue confirms equity weakness.")
