                tradeConversationPlaceholder(role: "Codex", kind: "Market End", title: "2026-05-06 Market End", body: "Verdict: Mixed. Notify: Yes. What happened: JPX/TSE cash session remained closed (substitute holiday); liquidity was thin and USD/JPY was volatile, with a sharp intraday dip on renewed intervention speculation before stabilizing in the mid-156s to high-157s. JGB cash/auctions: holiday/no new tape; last read still 10Y ~2.5% and 30Y ~3.7% (Apr 30). 7515.HK (Nikkei -2x inverse) and US EWV are still only proxies while Tokyo cash is shut. Trade read: Intervention risk supports the \"JPY can strengthen by June\" view, but without clearer BOJ follow-through the 160–162 band remains a live pressure zone; do not short Nikkei until cash reopen + post-earnings fatigue confirm. Next watch: Cash reopen May 7; Toyota results May 8 (1:55pm JST) and SoftBank May 13 (3:30pm/4:30pm JST); watch USD/JPY response to MOF language and JGB yields on reopen.")
                tradeConversationPlaceholder(role: "Codex", kind: "Market End", title: "2026-05-05 Market End", body: "Verdict: No Signal. Notify: No. What happened: TSE cash market closed for Children's Day (Golden Week); no Japan cash-session tape. USD/JPY held around ~157, with intervention risk still elevated if 160+ is tested again in thin liquidity. JGB: last visible cash read before the holidays had 10Y ~2.47% and 30Y ~3.64% (Apr 28); next stress points are MOF 10Y auction May 12 and 30Y auction May 14. Trade read: Thesis unchanged—JPY can still strengthen by June, but pressure can persist toward 160–162 while Fed is hawkish and BOJ is unclear; do not short Nikkei until post-results fatigue confirms. Next watch: May 7 cash reopen; Toyota results May 8 and Sony May 13 for risk sentiment/fatigue; keep 7515.HK (-2x inverse Nikkei) / EWV as watchlist instruments only.")
                tradeConversationPlaceholder(role: "Codex", kind: "Market End", title: "2026-05-05 Monitor repaired", body: "Verdict: No Signal. Notify: No. What happened: the 2026 JPY Trade Monitor was pointed at the wrong workspace and scheduled before Japan market close, so the Trade Thesis News section was not being updated. It is now scheduled for 14:45 HKT on weekdays from the Notion Journal repo and must write back into this News section plus Analysis Inbox. Japan cash equities are closed today for Children's Day; derivatives holiday trading is open, so the next visible market-end checkpoint should record holiday/no-cash-session context.")
                tradeConversationPlaceholder(role: "Codex", kind: "Setup", title: "Trade tab created", body: "The Notion Finance note is titled 2026 JPY Trade. The app tab is labeled 2026 Japan Trade so it is visible under Investment / Trade Thesis.")
                tradeConversationPlaceholder(role: "Me", kind: "Thesis", title: "JPY weakness toward 162", body: "Fed is hawkish and BOJ is still unclear, so JPY may see more pressure through 160 and possibly toward 162. We watch JGBs more closely to see when BOJ/MOF pressure becomes real.")
                tradeConversationPlaceholder(role: "Me", kind: "Timing", title: "May 8 / May 13 / May 22", body: "May 8 and May 13 are the short-Nikkei fatigue windows. May 22 Japan CPI confirms whether JPY can strengthen; before May 22, JPY may deteriorate further.")
                tradeConversationPlaceholder(role: "System", kind: "Cadence", title: "Twice-daily trade digest", body: "Every Japan trading day, write one midday and one market-end digest. Each digest must say what happened, whether it supports/counters/mixes/no-signals our JPY-by-June and short-Nikkei view, and whether anything is worth notifying now.")
                tradeConversationPlaceholder(role: "System", kind: "Risk", title: "Main failure mode", body: "If USD/JPY holds above 160 without intervention or rate pressure, JPY cash is exposed to further FX loss versus USD/HKD cash yield; short-Nikkei products add daily-reset and path-dependence risk.")
            }
            .padding(14)
            .frame(maxWidth: .infinity, alignment: .leading)
