    private func watchAdHocAnalysisReports(for row: NJInvestmentWatchRow) -> [NJInvestmentAnalysisReport] {
        switch row.symbol.uppercased() {
        case "0700 HK":
            return [
                NJInvestmentAnalysisReport(
                    id: "adhoc.0700.2026-05-03",
                    title: "IRC Analysis: Tencent slump, AI spend and day-trade levels",
                    source: "Codex ad hoc research",
                    dateText: "2026-05-03",
                    markdown: """
                    ## Tencent 0700.HK - Slump Analysis

                    **Price context:** IB Gateway historical bars showed Tencent closed at **HK$467.80 on 2026-04-30**, down about **28.8%** from the 6-month closing high of HK$657.00 on 2025-11-12. That close was also the 6-month low in the sampled IB data.

                    **Why it slumped**

                    - The core business is not obviously broken. Tencent's 2025 result still showed strength in games, ads, fintech and cloud.
                    - The market is worried about **capital allocation**: heavier AI investment in 2026 and possibly slower buybacks reduce near-term shareholder-return support.
                    - China tech has also been weak because investors are punishing AI spending without clear monetization.

                    **Day-trade levels**

                    - Support: **HK$467.7**, **HK$464.8**, **HK$463.2**
                    - Resistance: **HK$470.5**, **HK$474.6**, **HK$479.8-481.6**, **HK$493.4-495.0**
                    - Trigger: long scalp only if it reclaims HK$470.5 and holds above VWAP; stronger above HK$474.6.
                    - Failure: below HK$463.2 keeps the selloff active.

                    **Action read:** starter/watch only. Add confidence only if the May 13 result shows AI spend is not damaging core margin quality and the stock can hold a reclaim instead of fading.
                    """
                )
            ]
        case "3690 HK":
            return [
                NJInvestmentAnalysisReport(
                    id: "adhoc.3690.2026-05-03",
                    title: "IRC Analysis: Meituan price-war slump and rebound risk",
                    source: "Codex ad hoc research",
                    dateText: "2026-05-03",
                    markdown: """
                    ## Meituan 3690.HK - Slump Analysis

                    **Price context:** IB Gateway historical bars showed Meituan closed at **HK$83.26 on 2026-04-30**, down about **21.5%** from the 6-month closing high of HK$106.10 on 2026-01-06. The 60-day close low was HK$74.50 on 2026-03-05.

                    **Why it slumped**

                    - Meituan has the most damaged fundamental setup of the three HK names reviewed.
                    - Food delivery and instant-commerce competition with Alibaba and JD has hit margins directly.
                    - The market is repricing whether Meituan's unit economics can recover if competitors keep subsidizing orders.

                    **Day-trade levels**

                    - Support: **HK$82.25**, **HK$80.5**, **HK$80.2**, then HK$74.5
                    - Resistance: **HK$85.0**, **HK$87.2-87.9**, then HK$98.6
                    - Trigger: break and hold above HK$85.0 opens HK$87.2-87.9 retest.
                    - Failure: below HK$82.25 likely retests HK$80.5/HK$80.2.

                    **Action read:** highest-risk rebound trade. Sustained upside needs evidence that subsidies fall and local-commerce margins recover.
                    """
